description:
&lt;p&gt;Vacancies for Food Services Coordinator have become available based at Morriston Hospital. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Food Services Coordinator will be required to work independently within Catering Standard Operational Procedures and the principles of a flexible team approach and will be predominantly responsible for the operational organisation and supervisory management of the Food Service at Ward Level and all Commercial Catering Services (including; restaurant and coffee shop, vending and hospitality) within the Hospital base and any associated areas.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This will include ensuring that a high standard of customer service are maintained at all times throughout all areas.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Food Services Coordinator will deputise for the Hotel Services Supervisor/Food Services Team Leader as/when required.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Adhering to safe working practices and hygiene requirements in line with HACCP, all relevant Food Hygiene Legislation/Guidelines, and Health Board policies and protocols.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The completion of hard copy and electronic documentation as laid down, and taking appropriate action as required in compliance with HACCP protocols and, Departmental and Health Board policy. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The role will include undertaking duties in a chilled and/or frozen working and storage environment, as appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous Supervisory Experience is preferable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Linda ThomasFood Support Officer&lt;/p&gt;
